long_desc.thetext:
The build process is stopping if you try to get complex values from environment keys set by build time. This issue just occurs in build process not on source. 

e.g.

// Generator config:

"environment" : 
{
  "build.integration" : {
    "platform" : "XX",
    "bootstrap" : ["A", "B", "C"]
  }
}


// JS Code

var env = qx.core.Environment.get("build.integration");


// Generator error
<type 'exceptions.ValueError'> : Illegal value for JS constant: {'platform': 'XX', 'bootstrap': ['A', 'B', 'C']}

To prevent this error just refer qx.core.Environment to a local variable on the JS-script.
